e Guice explicitly. The standard generated test scaffold usually only includes the tested library and JUnit/assertj. To create meaningful tests, I need to add Guice, even though the existing build has Guice 5.1.0. Now, for new versions, I’m wondering if the driver fixing version will modify the same test project while keeping the build.gradle intact. \\n\\nSince there are existing tests, I need to figure out if additional setup is required for the library issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dependency management**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how adding a duplicate dependency from the driver might be a bad idea. The instruction is clear: \\\"Do not apply setup yourself — return decision.\\\" This means the driver applies a deterministic setup. If the dependency is already present, the idempotent driver should handle it.\\n\\nI now need to examine the API changes more closely. Notably, the method compile failure with `locator.add(Injector, int)` has been removed, now replaced by `MutableBeanLocator.add(BindingPublisher)`. I should look into whether I need to wrap the Injector in `InjectorBindings` with a `RankingFunction`, or if I should just use `Sisu.createInjector`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DjsCvtStwZlq0ixmXJ6eh4or|fc_06f4d26bdb392509016a2777dc30288194a32237c85b9ba3a2", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor url in [\n 'https://www.eclipse.org/sisu/apidocs/org.eclipse.sisu.inject/org/eclipse/sisu/inject/MutableBeanLocator.html',\n 'https://www.eclipse.org/sisu/org.eclipse.sisu.inject/apidocs/org/eclipse/sisu/inject/MutableBeanLocator.html',\n 'https://javadoc.io/doc/org.eclipse.sisu/org.eclipse.sisu.inject/0.9.0.M1/org/eclipse/sisu/inject/MutableBeanLocator.html'\n]:\n print('URL',url)\n try:\n  s=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=20).read().decode(errors='ignore')\n  print(s[:2000])\n  print('len',len(s))\n except Exception as e:\n  print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "o